20.title: Toy Hospital: Count Clarence's Daytime Adventure
20.plot: Count Clarence decides to stay up past his bedtime to play with the other toys during the day. Baby toy Dixie creates a mess in the Toy Nursery!

1.title: Knight Time/A Bad Case of the Pricklethorns
1.plot: Doc discovers that Donny's toy knight, Sir Kirby, is dirty. Doc diagnoses Boppy when he suddenly gets popped after landing in a rose bush.

2.title: Out of the Box/Run Down Race Car
2.plot: Little Jack, a jack in the box, can't pop, but he's scared of getting a check-up, so his dad, Big Jack, goes first. Ricardo Racecar loses his energy during a race.

3.title: Tea Party Tantrum/Blast Off!
3.plot: Doc wonders why Susie Sunshine is acting very cranky. Doc helps Carlos' toy space alien, Star Blazer Zero after his arms and legs falls off after a ride in his toy rocket.

4.title: Engine Nine, Feelin' Fine/The Right Stuff
4.plot: Doc and the toy gang come to a fire engine friend's rescue. Stuffy the Dragon looses his stuffing and learns that asking your friends for help is still being brave.

5.title: Gulpy Gulpy Gators!/One Note Wonder
5.plot: Doc fixes Gustave, the green gator on Donny's Gulpy Gulpy Gators game after he eats too many marbles. Alma's xylophone toy, Xyla, loses a key by accident.

6.title: Arcade Escapade/Starry, Starry Night
6.plot: Doc helps a stuffed toy Giraffe called Gaby after her leg was torn in a accident in the claw crane machine at the arcade. Doc helps Henry's Telescope Aurora when she suffers from blurry vision.

7.title: Ben/Anna Split/That's Just Clawful
7.plot: Ben and Anna, Alma's "Hugging Monkeys" need to be separated after one of them suffered a torn Velcro "hug" patch and needed to recover overnight at the clinic. Doc helps Hermie, her toy crab after his arm was torn out by Emmie & Alma's new puppy Rudi.

8.title: A Good Case of the Hiccups/Stuck Up
8.plot: Doc tries to fix Millie the Microphone when she can't stop repeating words. When Doc gets sand in her eye, she finds out what's wrong with Will's toy digger, Riggo, when his scoop gets stuck.

9.title: Rescue Ronda, Ready for Take-off!/All Washed Up
9.plot: Doc has to fix Luca's helicopter, Rescue Ronda, when she can't fly. Donny's toy robot, Robot Ray, learns the importance of following doctor's orders when he gets wet during a pirate game.

10.title: The New Girl/Wrap It Up
10.plot: Doc gets a doll from Japan called Kiko, and she wonders why her legs are so weak. Niles, Donny's toy crane, refuses to have his bandage removed.

11.title: Rest Your Rotors, Ronda!/Keep on Truckin
11.plot: Rescue Ronda learns how good it is to rest when her propeller is broken. Donny's truck, Tremaine, learns how to keep still to get repainted.

12.title: Blame It on the Rain/Busted Boomer
12.plot: Alma leaves her stuffed cow out in the rain; Doc cures a deflated soccer ball.

13.title: The Dark Knight/Hallie Gets an Earful
13.plot: During a sleepover party, Doc discovers that Sir Kirby is afraid of the dark and cures him of his fear of the dark. Doc helps Hallie hear better after she has trouble hearing.

14.title: Break Dancer/Bubble Monkey
14.plot: Bella, Doc's Ballerina doll, breaks her leg, and finds a lot to do while she waits for it to heal. Doc examines Emmie and Alma's bubble monkey after she stops blowing bubbles.

15.title: Out in the Wild/A Whale of a Time
15.plot: Doc helps Robot Ray after he injures his arm during a camping trip. Doc helps Lula, the sponge Beluga Whale grow.

16.title: The Rip Heard Around the World/Walkie Talkie Time
16.plot: Lambie accidentally gets ripped while dancing with Doc. Doc reunites a walkie talkie couple by finding a missing antenna.

17.title: Un-burr-able/Righty-on-Lefty
17.plot: While playing Astronautball, Stuffy falls into a bush and get burs all over his body. Doc helps Awesome Guy after she discovers that he can't walk correctly.

18.title: Hallie's Happy Birthday/Shark Style Tooth Ache
18.plot: It's Hallie's birthday and Doc and the gang throw a surprise party in her honor. Mr Chomp, Donny's toy shark, has a broken tooth that needs to repaired, but everyone (except for Doc and Hallie) are afraid of him.

19.title: Awesome Possum/The Bunny Blues
19.plot: A baby toy possum is lost and Doc frantically searches for the baby toy possum and reunites it with its mother. Doc discovers Alma's stuffed bunny in a box at a yard sale.

20.title: Get Set to Get Wet/Loud Louie
20.plot: Doc finds a mermaid doll and teaches her how to swim. A toy cellphone has a slight problem with its volume switch, causing him to talk real loud.

21.title: Caught Blue-Handed/To Squeak, or Not to Squeak
21.plot: A mysterious blue rash infects all the toys in the clinic. Marvin the Duck lost his squeaker at the water park and its up to Doc, Lambie and Stuffy to find it.

22.title: Doctoring the Doc/Hot Pursuit
22.plot: The crew from Doc's Clinic helps Doc after she falls ill. A toy police car overheats while pursuing the Wicked King.

23.title: Boo-Hoo to You!/It's Glow Time
23.plot: Doc helps a toy ghost, Sebastian, learn not to be scared on Halloween. Glo-Bo is very tired and weak, and unable to glow.

24.title: Chilly Gets Chilly/Through the Reading Glasses
24.plot: Chilly decides to hang out with the snowman that the gang built but nearly freezes in the cold. Doc receives a stuffed toy owl from her older cousin, but she can't read properly because of her poor eyesight.

25.title: My Huggy Valentine/Dusty Bear
25.plot: Lambie becomes jealous and brokenhearted when a new toy steals the spotlight from her during Valentine's Day. A teddy bear discovers why Donny doesn't want to play with him.

26.title: Bronto-Boo boos/Brontosaurus Breath
26.plot: When Bronty arrives to the McStuffin's household a mysterious outbreak of the Bronto-boo boos breaks out and infected the toys. After sharing a sandwich with Donny, Bronty comes down with a bad case of Bronto-breath.

1.title: Doc McStuffins Goes McMobile/Chip Off the Ol' Box
1.plot: Doc and her dad build a mobile clinic.

2.title: Awesome Guys Awesome Arm/Lamb in a Jam
2.plot: Awesome Guy lifts too many toys and hurts his arm.

3.title: Diagnosis Not Even Close-is/Bronty's Twisted Tail
3.plot: Hallie and Stuffy diagnose Robot Ray themselves while Doc is away.

4.title: Frida Fairy Flies Again/A Tale of Two Dragons
4.plot: Alma's fairy flier gets caught on a branch that rips a hole in its wing!

5.title: Think Pink/You Foose, You Lose
5.plot: When Chilly is accidentally washed in the washing machine with Doc's red scarf, he turns pink!

6.title: Leilani's Lu'au/Karate Kangaroos
6.plot: Doc receives a solar-powered hula girl and the toys want to have a luau in the clinic.

7.title: Doc to the Rescue/Don't Knock the Noggin
7.plot: Doc takes the Doc Mobile to rescue Dress-Up Daisy from a tree.

8.title: The Glider Brothers/Disco Dress Up Daisy
8.plot: Doc unknowingly brings Donny's new daredevil glider planes to her indoor picnic.

9.title: Kirby and the King/Bubble Monkey, Blow Your Nose!
9.plot: Sir Kirby and The Wicked King get stuck together with paste and must work together to get free. Doc brings Bubble Monkey to visit Donny to cheer him up after he catches a cold, but Bubble Monkey gets a sneezing fit.

10.title: Professor Pancake/You Crack Me Up
10.plot: Doc finds Professor Hootsburgh trapped and flattened under her toy box.

11.title: A Very McStuffins Christmas
11.plot: Doc and the gang travel to the Santa's workshop in the North Pole.

12.title: The Doctor Will See You Now/L'il Egghead Feels the Heat
12.plot: Doc visits Dr. Peerless and sees her old toy friends Carl, Dolly, and Morton when they get sticky spots all over them.

13.title: The Big Sleepover/No Sweetah Cheetah
13.plot: Doc goes to a sleepover at Emmie's but she misses her family and friends.

14.title: Big Head Hallie/Peaches Pie, Take a Bath!
14.plot: Hallie sees that her toy has its own TV show.

15.title: Celestial Celeste/Run Doc Run!
15.plot: Doc brings home a space toy to help with her solar system project.

16.title: A Fairy Big Knot/Rosie the Rescuer
16.plot: When Frida Fairy Flier shows off her tricks to Doc and the toys, her strings get into an enormous tangle.

17.title: Crikey! It's Wildlife Will!/Rootin' Tootin' Southwest Sal
17.plot: Doc wants to find a way for Wildlife Will to keep up his exploring ways.

18.title: Take Your Doc to Work Day/Blazer's Bike
18.plot: Doc is thrilled to spend a day at her Mom's office, where she meets a doll named Curly Q.

19.title: Dad's Favorite Toy
19.plot: During spring-cleaning, Dad, Donny and Doc find Dad's favorite boyhood toy, Saltwater Serge and Wellington Whale, in the attic.

20.title: Dads Favorite Toy/Chilly and the Dude
20.plot: During spring-cleaning, Dad, Donny and Doc find Dad's favorite boyhood toy, Saltwater Serge and Wellington Whale, in the attic.

21.title: Sir Kirby and the Plucky Princess/Serpent Sam Makes a Splash
21.plot: Princess Persephone and Sir Kirby have a Knight and Princess play-off competition. Donny gets a new snake shaped water gun toy named Serpent Sam, but he has trouble spraying water.

22.title: The Wicked King and the Mean Queen/Take a Stroll!
22.plot: The Wicked King and the Mean Queen play a game to determine who should receive a royal ball.

23.title: Mirror, Mirror on My Penguin/Hide and Eek
23.plot:

24.title: Doc's Busy Day/Wrong Side of the Law
24.plot: When Doc's toddler cousin Sabrina comes to visit, she plays with all of Doc's toys and breaks them.

25.title: The Doctor Will See You Now
25.plot: Doc visits Dr. Peerless and sees her old toy friends Carl, Dolly, and Morton when they get sticky spots all over them.

26.title: Hazel Has a Sleepover/My Breakfast With Bronty
26.plot: Doc discovers why Hazel the elephant doesn't want to go to Emmie's sleepover. At breakfast, Doc brings the toys to life and Bronty is super excited to be on the breakfast table.

29.title: Training Army Al/Sproingo Boingo Takes the Leap
29.plot: Army Al volunteers to go on a camping trip with Donny, but everyone is worried he'll come back hurt. The Wicked King dares Sproingo Boingo to jump off a really high block tower.

30.title: Shell Shy/Commander No
30.plot: During the toy "Splash Dance" competition, Doc teaches Theo how to overcome his "shy-guys" and speak up to Hermie. Commander Crush realizes he doesn't like to be tickled.

33.title: A Day Without Cuddles/Collide-o-scope
33.plot: It's international Cuddle Day - Lambie's favorite holiday! When Doc arrives home from the science museum, she introduces a new toy, Kiara the kaleidoscope.

34.title: Toy in the Sun
34.plot: Viewy Stewie gets two discs jammed while Doc and the toys view images from Doc's grandma. Doc wants to keep her dollar safe and Nikki the piggy bank will do anything to protect it.

37.title: The Big Storm/Spritzy Mitzi
37.plot: Chilly and Hallie are storm buddies when a big storm is approaching.

44.title: Oooey Gablooey Springs a Leak/There's a King in Your Tummy
44.plot: When Oooey springs a leak, blue goo oozes out from his insides and he gets queasy and panics.

1.title: Let The Nightingale Sing
1.plot: When Doc is reading a book about the famous nurse, Florence Nightingale, Doc's magic takes her and the toys to England in the 1800s. Hallie inspires her to assist Doc as a nurse.

5.title: The Flimsy Grumpy Bat/Rockstar Ruby and the Toys
5.plot: When Clarence, a cardboard bat, accidentally gets wet, he is unable to stand. When Rockstar Ruby's microphone button breaks, Ruby is crushed and can't do her show the right way.

6.title: Take Your Pet to the Vet/Master and Commander
6.plot: Doc brings home her class pet, a hamster named Coleslaw. Doc and the Toys have a contest to see who is the best commander of Doc's new "Command Center" space toy.

7.title: Itty Bitty Bess Takes Flight
7.plot: There's a new toy in Doc's room and her name is Itty Bitty Bess! When Doc and the Toys decide to throw a McStuffins Toy Ball, Doc introduces Flora, a beautiful Flamenco dancer.

8.title: Fully in Focus/Picky Nikki
8.plot: Viewy Stewie gets two discs jammed while Doc and the toys view images from Doc's grandma. Doc wants to keep her dollar safe and Nikki the piggy bank will do anything to protect it.

15.title: The New Nurse/Chilly's Loose Button
15.plot: The New Nurse Dress Up Declan, a new toy, steps in as Doc's nurse after Hallie gets injured. Dress Up Daisy learns boys can be nurses, too. Chilly's Loose Button Lambie accidentally snags Chilly's button leaving it hanging by a thread.

16.title: Mind Over Matter
16.plot:

17.title: Snowy Gablooey/Gooooooooal!
17.plot: During a snowball fight with Doc, Donny accidentally got snow in his coat and as he went inside, he accidentally left Oooey Gablooey in a snowdrift causing him to freeze up.

18.title: Hallie Halloween/Don't Fence Me In
18.plot: Hallie's computer chip that's supposed to be in her chest falls into her foot...and her foot starts talking! Donny brings home Pop-up Paulo, a frog that pops up and surprises him.

19.title: Twin Tweaks
19.plot: When Fetchin' Findo goes after his bone in the sandbox, he gets sand in his nose that causes sensor malfunction. Oooey Gablooey decides to put on a show with the Twirly Twins.

20.title: Blast Off to the Unknown!/Bust a Move
20.plot: Doc's neighbor, Carlos, is moving away and before he leaves Doc agrees to fix his toy Star Blazer Zero. A new family moves into Carlos' house, bringing along a toy names Ferris!

21.title: Doc McStuffins Goes to Washington
21.plot: Doc visits the White House and meets First Lady Michelle Obama. Doc meets a new toy named Winnie who helps blow up balloons for Donny's birthday party!

22.title: Mirror, Mirror on My Penguin/Hike and Eek!
22.plot: When Doc gives Waddly Penguin a check-up, she notices the mirror on his tummy is smudged.

24.title: Hooty's Duty/A Cure for a King
24.plot: Nurse Hattie throws Doc's mom a baby shower! When the Wicked King steals Queen Amina's crown, he loses his own crown in the process.

25.title: St. Patrick's Day Dilemma/A Giant Save
25.plot: It's St. Patrick's Day and Doc brings home an Irish paper doll named Fiona. The toys are excited to meet Doc's new toy, Gillian the Giant.

26.title: Runaway Love
26.plot: While preparing for the arrival of the new baby, Donny fears that his parents are forgetting about him. After attending a biking event with her Dad, Doc gets a new toy Stella!

27.title: The Lady in the Lake/Black Belt Kangaroos
27.plot: Doc and her family go to the lake for vacation! When the Black Belt Kangaroos find out that Hallie is a black belt, they can't wait to learn her karate skills.

28.title: Joni the Pony/Sleepless in Stuffyland
28.plot: Joni the pony trips over her mane, so the other toys suggest a haircut, but Joni worries that it will hurt. Doc decides to bring Stuffy for her school presentation, but he finds it hard to sleep the night before.

29.title: The Search for Squibbles; Factory Fabulous
29.plot: It's Stuffy's first day as Squibbles' new owner, but he's not sure how to take care of a pet. When the King and Queen's castle falls down, Queen Amina leads the rebuilding efforts.

1.title: Welcome to McStuffinsville
1.plot: Grandma gives Doc and her toys the surprise of a lifetime by taking them to McStuffinsville, a town made up entirely of toys, and puts Doc in charge of the McStuffins Toy Hospital!

2.title: First Day of Med School/Stuffy Gets His Scrubs
2.plot: A busy day at the hospital shows the toys that they need training to help Doc. Stuffy tries to find his place at McStuffins Toy Hospital.

4.title: Toy Hospital: Night Shift/Check Up Chilly
4.plot: On their first night shift, Lambie is in charge of the Hospital Nursery but can't get the babies to sleep. Chilly schedules too many appointments for himself!

5.title: Project Nursery Makeover/Stuffy's Ambulance Ride
5.plot: The Nursery gets a delivery: four identical baby dolls that Lambie has trouble telling apart! After Stuffy is hurt in Royal Land, he is nervous to get a ride in an ambulance.

6.title: Toy Hospital: Made to Be a Nurse/Rescue at the Ranch
6.plot: When a new nurse upstages Hallie, she no longer feels needed and disappears! When there's trouble at Southwest Sal's, the toys travel to the ranch to help.

7.title: Toy Hospital: CeCe's First Bath/The Most Impatient Patient
7.plot: When Baby Toy CeCe falls in the mud, she needs to have her very first bath! After getting a crown-cussion, the Wicked King ends up being a pain to everyone at the hospital!

9.title: Toy Hospital: A Lesson in Diagnosis/Karaoke Katie's Opening Night
9.plot: The Med Students learn how to diagnose a patient. The toys take care of Karaoke Katie, a doll with an attachable karaoke machine.

11.title: Toy Hospital: Bouncy House Boo Boos/The Best Therapy Pet Yet
11.plot: When some of the toys get hurt at Bobby's birthday party, Doc teaches them about bounce house safety.

12.title: The Lake Monster
12.plot:

13.title: Toy Hospital: Chuck Learns to Look!/Birthday Party Emergency
13.plot: Chuck the wind-up chicken keeps crossing the street without looking! Doc and the Toys discover a broken birthday present and rush to fix it before its kid returns!

14.title: Toy Hospital: Camille Gets Over the Hump/Willow's Wonky Whiskers
14.plot: Doc and the Med Students travel to a desert playset to see a toy camel named Camille. When Doc is unable to see inside a toy's fluffy cheek, she decides to do a CAT scan.

15.title: Into the Hundred Acre Wood!
15.plot: Doc and gang help rescue Pooh from floating away with a bunch of balloons.

17.title: Toy Hospital: Mole Money, Mole Problems/Yip Yip Boom
17.plot: "Mole Money, Mole Problems" - When a toy mole is having trouble getting around without bumping into everything, Doc diagnoses her and calls on Stuffy to find her a guide pet. "Yip, Yip, Boom!" - During the light show finale, Squibbles gets scared and runs amok through McStuffinsville.

18.title: Hannah the Brave/Waddly's Huggy Overload
18.plot: Hannah the doll needs Doc's help getting gum out of her hair! Doc is chosen to lead the Rescue Workers Parade in McStuffinsville but some of the crowd gets a little too excited.

21.title: Get-Well Gus Gets Well; Triceratops Trouble
21.plot: Get-Well Gus, a flying Pegasus toy that delivers gifts to the hospital, crashes and loses his wing. Doc and the toys have trouble diagnosing a triceratops train.

23.title: First Responders to the Rescue
23.plot: When a toy is left out in the rain in the real world, the toys go to rescue him!

26.title: Emergency Plan
26.plot: The Doll family is separated from one another when their house collapses. A toy duck tries fixing other toys without training.
